#
# This directory contains three different versions of LULESH-1.0, all
# using RAJA:
#
# 1) luleshRAJA-serial.cxx contains a serial-only version.
# 2) luleshRAJA-parallel.cxx.src contains a version that can be run 
#    in 9 different parallel variants using RAJA (different data layouts,
#    different OpenMP parallelization strategies (including lock-free
#    dependency graphs), CilkPlus, and GPU using CUDA). See luleshPolicy.hxx
#    more more details and how to select the exeuction mode.
# 3) luleshRAJA-parallel-FT.cxx contains a version of #2, but with a
#    loop-level fault tolerance mechanism enabled. All loops in the FT
#    version are idempotent.  
#

##
## To build and run the serial CPU variant:
##
## 1) Set RAJA_ARCH for the compiler and platform in the Makefile.
## 2) type ./build-serial
## 3) type ./run-serial
##

##
## To build and run any of the parallel CPU variants:
##
## 1) Set RAJA_ARCH for the compiler and platform in the Makefile.
## 2) Set the USE_VASE value in luleshPolicy.hx
## 3) type ./build-parallel
## 4) type ./run-parallel
##
## To build and run on the GPU version (e.g., ipa or rzhasgpu)
##
## 1) Set RAJA_ARCH = ipa_nvcc
## 2) Set the USE_VASE value to 9 in luleshPolicy.hxx
## 3) type ./build-parallel-gpu
## 4) Allocate a node on the machine. E.g., on ipa
> salloc -p nvidia -N1
> setenv CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES 0
## 5) type ./run-parallel-gpu 
##
